# BarberGarage CMS & API

BarberGarage (`barbergarage.bg`) is a client site whose **content source of truth** lives in apigoalgus (`api.goalgus.bg`). The static folder `barbergarage/` is the layout shell; Phase 2 will fetch JSON from the API server-side. Do not edit static HTML for copy that belongs in the CMS.

## Architecture

- **Content & settings** → `site_contents`, `site_settings` tables; edited in `/dashboard/sites/barbergarage`.
- **Media** → `storage/app/public/sites/barbergarage/{images|videos}/` on the `public` disk; served via **HMAC signed URLs** (`/sites/barbergarage/m/{id}?signature=...`), not via Bearer token in the browser.
- **API** → `GET /api/v1/site/content` or `/api/v1/site/content/{locale}` with `Authorization: Bearer <token>`. Token is for BarberGarage **server-side** fetch only — never expose in client JS.
- **Human owner** → `todor@barbergarage.bg` (`TodorUserSeeder`, role `admin`).

## Static frontend (Phase 2 — live)

The `barbergarage/` folder is a thin PHP shell that fetches JSON from the API server-side and renders the HTML.

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `barbergarage/index.php` | BG entry point — calls `bg_load_content('bg')` and renders the shared template |
| `barbergarage/en/index.php` | EN entry point — calls `bg_load_content('en')` and renders the shared template |
| `barbergarage/lib/api-client.php` | Reads `config.php`, fetches `/api/v1/site/content/{locale}` with Bearer token, caches in `barbergarage/cache/site-{locale}.json` for `cache_ttl` seconds; falls back to stale cache on API failure |
| `barbergarage/lib/render.php` | Escape + content/setting/media helpers used by the template |
| `barbergarage/lib/template.php` | Single HTML template shared by both locales (no duplication) |
| `barbergarage/config.sample.php` | Committed template: `api_base`, `api_token`, `cache_ttl`, `maps_api_key` |
| `barbergarage/config.php` | **Gitignored** real config; copy from sample and fill in the raw Bearer token |
| `barbergarage/cache/` | File cache + `.htaccess` deny-all + `.gitignore` (folder kept, contents ignored) |
| `barbergarage/.htaccess` | `DirectoryIndex index.php index.html`, denies access to `config*.php` and `/lib/` |
| `barbergarage/js/site.js` | Nav, parallax, lightbox — gallery DOM is server-rendered, JS only wires interactions |

Conventions:

- **Token is server-only.** Never expose `api_token` in client JS or HTML output.
- **Stale-while-error.** If the API is unreachable, the PHP shell keeps serving the last cached JSON, regardless of age. Total outages only happen on first load before any cache exists.
- **Maps key stays on the BarberGarage side** (`config.php`), restricted by HTTP referrer in Google Cloud Console. The dashboard owns lat/lng/zoom; the BarberGarage shell composes the embed URL.
- **Brand assets** (`hero_bg`, `about_photo`, `logo`, `favicon`) are single-slot uploads managed in the Sites dashboard (`/dashboard/sites/barbergarage/media`). The PHP shell consumes them through the API; the only client-side static fallback is when a slot is empty. Use `POST /dashboard/sites/{slug}/media/brand/{purpose}` to replace; uploading a new file deletes the previous row + storage object.
- **Deploy:** `deploy/deploy-barbergarage.sh` rsync excludes `config.php` and `cache/*` so production secrets and cache survive across deploys.
- **First production deploy:** SSH in, `cp config.sample.php config.php`, edit and paste the raw token from the dashboard. The cache directory must be writable by the PHP user.

## Database tables

| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `sites` | One row per managed site (`slug`: `barbergarage`) |
| `site_tokens` | Hashed API tokens; raw shown once on create |
| `site_settings` | JSON key/value: contact, map, hours, caps, social URLs |
| `site_contents` | Localized copy: `locale` (`bg`/`en`), `section`, `field`, `value` |
| `site_media` | Images/videos with `purpose`, `sort_order`, alt text BG/EN |

No foreign keys — indexed `site_id` columns only (shared-hosting pattern).

## Locales & sections

- **Default locale:** `bg`. Always maintain **both** `bg` and `en` when adding fields.
- **Sections:** `hero`, `welcome`, `about`, `gallery`, `video`, `hours`, `map`, `nav`, `footer`, `meta`.

## Media limits

- Gallery cap default **150** (`site_settings.gallery_cap`).
- Video cap default **10** (`site_settings.video_cap`).

## Access control

- Dashboard Sites pages: `sites.view` / `sites.manage` → `super_admin`, `admin` only.
- See `aa-user-roles-rule.mdc` access matrix for full list.
- Route middleware: `role:super_admin,admin` on all `/dashboard/sites/*` routes.
- API routes: `api.site` middleware (`EnsureSiteToken`).

